# =============================================================================
# .dockerignore — excludes everything the build doesn't need.
# =============================================================================
# Keeps the build context small (faster transfer to the Docker daemon) and
# reduces the surface for accidental secrets in build layers.
# Copy / symlink this file to the repository root when the docker build is
# invoked from there: `docker build -f deploy/docker/Dockerfile.api .`.
# =============================================================================

# Build outputs --------------------------------------------------------------
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/out/
**/publish/
**/TestResults/

# Node / front-end intermediate artifacts ------------------------------------
**/node_modules/
**/dist/
**/.next/

# IDE / OS clutter -----------------------------------------------------------
**/.vs/
**/.vscode/
**/.idea/
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db

# Docs, tests, deploy artefacts — not needed at build time -------------------
**/*.md
tests/
docs/
deploy/
ops/

# Git + CI metadata ----------------------------------------------------------
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.github/
.gitlab/

# Secrets — belt-and-suspenders. Must NEVER be committed anyway. -------------
**/*.env
**/*.pfx
**/*.key
**/appsettings.*.local.json
